< text>
Danielle is my weight loss counselor.  I've lost 42 pounds since Feb 1, 2017, so 4 months and I am now at my goal weight!  I started at 241 and I'm now at 199 pounds.  I am a 47-year-old 6'3" guy. Danielle has been wonderful because she is so motivating and so friendly.  She's a great communicator and always keeps our weekly appointments right on time.  When I sit down for my appointments with her after I weigh in, she always asked me what kind of eating challenges I've been having and what potential challenges might be coming up in the coming week.   She always offers great ideas about how to stay on the program and still be able to live your life comfortably socially. What I like most about Medifast is that it has been a structured and simple weight-loss program.  Because it's so structured it has been easy for me to follow and stay focused and especially because I had such immediate results that right away I didn't want to make a mistake and cheat on my weight loss plan. So, I never did.  The Medifast meals are really pretty good tasting for the most part.  Eating every 2 hours has been a huge lifestyle change for me for the better. That way I never get too over-hungry and so I never overeat anymore.  I have referred my Mom and another good friend to Medifast and Danielle.  They have also been very successful. A friend of mine referred me and he was very successful.  Everyone else on staff there is also very friendly and encouraging.  Highly recommended!</text>

< Text>
Over three years ago I'd had enough of my excessive weight.  I thought I'd tried everything...except Medifast.  I went into the El Cajon office, spoke with the supervisor, got a feel for the place, people, and program and decided to try it.  That was the best decision I'd made in a long time. I was able to maintain my weight for two years, but this last summer I allowed outside stressors to take over again, and decided I needed to get a handle on it before it got a handle on me.  I'd only gained back 10 pounds, but it was enough, so I went back.  I reactivated my plan, and am currently working with Crystal.  Both coaches have been absolutely wonderful, and I would recommend Medifast to anyone and everyone who is interested.  It doesn't matter if you have 100 pounds to loose or 10.  The program can work for everyone.  I like the food, and I thrive in the stricter environment (in terms of allowed/not allowed foods).  It allows me to adjust my eating habits to good ones, and gives me enough time to get the cravings of sugars out of my mind/body.  The body analysis that they conduct also allow you to see how any change you make in your diet can effect your body.  I have relost those 10 pounds and am maintaining again!<//Text>

<Review>I can't say enough positive about this center and our experience overall with Medifast.

First, to eliminate some confusion, this is NOT attending group meetings where you report back. This is NOT an all liquid diet. Each weekly session with your counselor is private, informative and never rushed.

My wife and daughter signed up and then left for a college tour. One week later, I decided I'd support them and I signed up too. We all ended up with Nikki as our counselor. We all can't say enough good about her! She's great! But please don't think this means the other counselors aren't equally as good because they are. All of the people at this facility are exceptional.

We all lost out weight at about the same rate. I have reached my goal weight and am in the transitional phase.

The center and the counselors do a great job of keeping you motivated. If your weight loss slows, they know exactly what to do to mix it up. With their body composition scanner, if your muscle mass drops, they know exactly how to adjust your meals to maintain your muscle and eliminate just the fat.

FOOD:
We like all of the food with only a couple of exceptions, but the selection is more than adequate. You won't get bored with the food. There's plenty of variety and preparation options for their meals. With the assistance of our counselor, we have become very creative with our own prepared 'lean and green' meal.

REFERRALS:
Many of our friends have seen our success and that has promoted three so far to sign up for Medifast. They are happy they did and have also had success.< /Review><Response>None</Response>< user_id>

I hope to use these lessons in my personal life as well.  I look forward to and am well on my way to my final goal, which is now only 34lbs away. 1325102041393<//Date>
< rating>
3</rating>
< Text>
-BEDROOM:   Overpriced.   We had a 'deluxe double' bedroom which I thought was more roomy than it was. ...    It was one room, No fan in bathroom, but rooms were really warm in a good way.     Great beds,  great comforters.    Nice lounge chair and desk with two chairs.   Nice touch with the robes.
- PEOPLE WITH ANIMALS:  We  brought our dog and were only charged 75$ for 3 nights.   We were not charged 75$ per night per dog like the website said.      There is not a limit of 5 dogs per day total at the lodge, like the website says,   and I counted way more than 5.     All guests with dogs seemed to be housed in one row,  on the first floor,  rooms 177 to 191,  and the back yard area was grass with too much doggie doodoo that guests weren't picking up.     LOVED the doggie doodoo bags,   the dog bed,  dog toys and water bowl.    They were very welcoming to our dog and that was great!!
-VIEW:  The lodge is renovating the pool and the back side,  and our view was a green fence with dirt and tractors.    For the price,  I was very disappointed in the view out of our back sliding glass window and thought the lodge should have said something to us, or reduced the price.      There was no tractor construction while we were there, no noise,  but,  still the view was horrible.
-HAD TO WALK OUTSIDE LODGE TO GET TO ROOM -- I thought it was strange that we had to walk outside the lodge to get to our room...  You'd think that with a hotel in Yosemite,  you could walk inside or outside to get to the main lodge area/restaurants...
-NICE STAFF  --   great staff.
-VALET:    VALET IS free,  but warning,  we used it once, called 1/2 hour in advance and when we went out,  it wasn't there....    so we self parked and didnt use valet the rest of the day.
-FOOD:    the food was nothing to write home about.
-CHRISTMAS BUFFET:   really nice.     great staff,   very good food, but again,  pretty average.
-ACTIVITIES:   we went ice skating in Yosemite,   and did ROCK CLIMBING at the lodge,..    super fun.< /Text>

<Rating>4<//Rating>< review>
Everything was great except having to wait in line so long for a popcorn refill- you should be able to stand on the side and get it filled fast- after all, for the expense, you're missing the movie waiting on the REFILL...a bit angering. I do like that you can get breaks on concessions by joining their free club-1 large soda- and 1 large popcorn was 12.50. HOWEVER- the 3D IMAX seats are ridiculously priced-$72+ for 1 senior, 1 adult and 2 kids- that's just for the tickets! At least their reclining seats are very comfy, and the bathrooms were clean. And you can park in the parking garage on the street to the east of there for free if you stamp it in the validator machine at the desk just inside the door, that's handy. It's hard to find a parking place otherwise...< /review>

<user>106554993982084902424</user>< Name>
Marvin Avila<//Name>
< time>
1540756021434</time>
<rate>3< /rate>< Review>
This is a good place to bring your family for a good time and to watch movies. Good atmosphere, good quality picture, sound, and recliners which I think are cool. They have a pretty cool arcade for the kids or the big kid in you. Their food court needs improvement they can organize and train their staff to help the long lines flow smoother because the wait times are crazy up to 30 minutes on busy nights. They offer an option to reserve your seats when you purchase tickets online and even though this is a good idea it also creates an awkward situation when you get there and someone is sitting in your seats. Most people are understanding and just get up and move when you ask for your seats but I've seen people get angry and hostile and cause a scene. It got so bad to the point security had to get involved. I was there with my kids and I'm really not ok with exposing my family to that. I personally think there is more they can do make reserved seating better for everyone.< /Review>

< text>
Nice and clean, but we were the first in the theater for the day so nothing to compare it to.

You PICK THE EXACT SPOT you want to sit and no one else may sit in the chair number you picked as it is printed on your ticket stubs.

However, the chairs (not seats) are PLUSH RECLINERS! There is plenty of room in front of the chairs so there is no kicking or bumping of the back of your seat. Needless to say the isles are wide and spacious. No turning sideways or having someone's butt in your face on their way to their chair.</text>
